"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-12-2024-olympics-tinubu-celebrates-rena-wakama-for-winning-best-coach-prize\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  on  By  President Bola Tinubu has celebrated Rena Wakama for winning the best coach in the women's basketball event at the 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 29, \"end\": 40, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bola_Tinubu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bola Tinubu\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bola_Tinubu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bola_Tinubu\"}, {\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaelva\", \"score\": 0.9999999813869638, \"rank\": 1.854898478985931e-08, \"text\": \"Rena\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaelva\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaelva\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wakama, who is the D'Tigress head coach, led the Nigerian side to a historic quarter final outing at the Games before bowing to the US.\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 174, \"end\": 183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"D'Tigress\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria_women's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"score\": 0.9739083855377193, \"rank\": 0.026790625124146487, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\"}, {\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9898642177236995, \"rank\": 0.004847230695221679, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"D'Tigress made history as the first African team to reach the quarter finals in the history of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reacting to the development on Monday, a statement issued by the Special Adviser on Media and Publicity to the President, Ajuri Ngelale, said, \\\"The recognition of Ms. Wakama, 32, by the International Basketball Federation, FIBA, further accents her well established leadership qualities and dedication to excellence.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Basketball Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The President also commends the team, and all those who played a part in the unprecedented feat at the Olympics, enjoining them not to relent or become crestfallen but to remain resilient and determined for greatness.\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The President further thanks the Nigerian contingent and wished them success in their respective endeavours.\\\"\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 974, \"end\": 982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"score\": 0.9739083855377193, \"rank\": 0.026790625124146487, \"text\": \"Nigerian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigerians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transfer: Maresca to cut down Chelsea squad to 24 players  Transfer: Man City defender leaves Guardiola's side for new club ahead of Chelsea clash  Shettima arrives Lagos to brief Tinubu on Maiduguri security situation  Bala Mohammed hails Tinubu for tackling insecurity in Bauchi  Electricity Supply: Osun APC chieftain decries problem, demands Tinubu's intervention  An African business icon-Tinubu hails billionaire Tony Elumelu on his 64th birthday  Fuel price: Tinubu moves to end burden on Nigerians  2027: Vote Tinubu or face spiritual judgment - Portable tells Yorubas  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1082, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9990333035173438, \"rank\": 0.0009675865857548727, \"text\": \"Chelsea\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9999999999943157, \"rank\": 5.745846061264712e-12, \"text\": \"Man City\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manchester_City_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 1146, \"end\": 1155, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pep_Guardiola\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guardiola\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pep_Guardiola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pep_Guardiola\"}, {\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9990333035173438, \"rank\": 0.0009675865857548727, \"text\": \"Chelsea\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chelsea_F.C.\"}, {\"begin\": 1217, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lagos\", \"score\": 0.99370150612861